title: TOF x Energy Hydrogen Rates (with spin accumulations plotted at end of accumulation in sector order) - Lou Lanzerotti (New Jersey Institute of Technology)

info.contact: Lou Lanzerotti @ New Jersey Institute of Technology

parameters.name: Time
parameters.x_description: Ephemeris Time of the start  of the accumulation for this measurement.

parameters.name: FPDU
parameters.description: FPDU: Proton flux spectrograms in energy, by telescope in sector order

bins.name: Telescope
bins.description: Identifies the telescope used to collect the measurement

bins.name: FPDU_Energy_Fixed
bins.description: Midpoint energy of the measurement channel. A value of -1 indicates that an energy definition for this channel is not applicable

parameters.name: FPDU_Error
parameters.description: ---> The percentage error of the measurement.

bins.name: Telescope
bins.description: Identifies the telescope used to collect the measurement

bins.name: FPDU_Energy_Fixed
bins.description: Midpoint energy of the measurement channel. A value of -1 indicates that an energy definition for this channel is not applicable

parameters.name: FPDU_Quality
parameters.description: ---> Quality flag for the measurement for each telescope/channel/timestep. .see PREBM standards for definition

bins.name: Telescope
bins.description: Identifies the telescope used to collect the measurement

bins.name: FPDU_Energy_Fixed
bins.description: Midpoint energy of the measurement channel. A value of -1 indicates that an energy definition for this channel is not applicable

parameters.name: Sector
parameters.description: ---> The current sector number where each spin is divided into 36 sectors.

parameters.name: Duration
parameters.description: ---> Duration of the accumulation.

parameters.name: Spin
parameters.description: ---> The current spin number of the spacecraft

parameters.name: Position_SM
parameters.description: Position of the spacecraft in SM coordinates

parameters.name: Position
parameters.description: ---> Position of the SC in the GEO Reference Frame.

parameters.name: Position_GSM
parameters.description: ---> Position of the SC in the GSM Reference Frame.

parameters.name: Position_Quality
parameters.description: ---> The position quality flag, 0=good, 1=bad.

parameters.name: OrbitNumber
parameters.description: Orbit Number at the time of the measurement

parameters.name: L
parameters.description: ---> Dipole L value calculated using the SM Reference Frame

parameters.name: L_Eq
parameters.description: ---> McElqain L value calculated at the Equator (derived from ECT MagEphem data).

parameters.name: L_Star
parameters.description: ---> Roeder's L* value (derived from ECT MagEphem data) for the average pitch angle.

parameters.name: I
parameters.description: ---> Integral invariant for the average pitch angle derived from ECT MagEphem data.

parameters.name: K
parameters.description: ---> The Second Invariant ( I*sqrt(Bm) ) for the average pitch angle derived from ECT MagEphem data.

parameters.name: MLT
parameters.description: ---> Magnetic Local Time of S/C in Centerted Dipole Coordinates derived from ECT MagEphem data.

parameters.name: FPDU_Alpha
parameters.description: The pitch angle based upon the look direction of each telescope, alpha=cos-1(B*(-look))

bins.name: Telescope
bins.description: Identifies the telescope used to collect the measurement

parameters.name: Alpha_Quality
parameters.description: ---> A flag describing the Quality of the Pitch Angle as calculated, 0=good, 1=bad.

parameters.name: ParticleDir_SM
parameters.description: The particle velocity unit vector for each telescope look direction (i.e. the negative of the telescope look direction unit vector). (No CDAWeb Plotting)
parameters.x_cdf_DISPLAY_TYPE: default_dimension y=ParticleDir_SM(*,1), y=ParticleDir_SM(*,2), y=ParticleDir_SM(*,3), y=ParticleDir_SM(*,4), y=ParticleDir_SM(*,5), y=ParticleDir_SM(*,6), z=NumAxisFixed

parameters.name: L_StarArr
parameters.description: Roeder's L* value (derived from ECT MagEphem data) for each of the telescopes based upon the telescope pitch angle.

parameters.name: IArr
parameters.description: ---> The Integral invariant for the pitch angle of each telescope derived from ECT MagEphem data.

parameters.name: KArr
parameters.description: ---> Second Invariant ( I*sqrt(Bm) ) for the pitch angle of each telescope derived from ECT MagEphem data.

parameters.name: Position_SM_TT
parameters.description: [Labels on plots] Position of the spacecraft in SM coordinates. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['Position_SM']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
